                            <comment id="17956130" author="michael-o" created="Wed, 4 Jun 2025 14:59:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t understand the issue. How is the client support to detect a sensitive header?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17956139" author="olegk" created="Wed, 4 Jun 2025 15:36:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=michael-o&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;michael-o&quot;&gt;michael-o&lt;/a&gt; The problem here is that the client treats `&lt;a href=&quot;https://news.google.com:443&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://news.google.com:443&lt;/a&gt;` and `&lt;a href=&quot;https://news.google.com&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://news.google.com&lt;/a&gt;` as different authorities. In case of a redirect it only matters if sensitive headers are present.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It is a matter of normalizing the authority of the redirected request.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Oleg&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17956171" author="michael-o" created="Wed, 4 Jun 2025 17:38:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I see, I almost thought so.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17956297" author="JIRAUSER309937" created="Thu, 5 Jun 2025 09:11:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Another case that is kind of related to this bug where you might want to consider allowing &lt;tt&gt;HttpClient&lt;/tt&gt; to follow the redirect is when it is going from &lt;tt&gt;http&lt;/tt&gt; to &lt;tt&gt;https&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17956313" author="michael-o" created="Thu, 5 Jun 2025 10:41:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;A protocol upgrade should be safe, but not a downgrade.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
